column5: With these south winds yesterday the walleye bite has  been goooood  My buddies and me don't  keep to many fish but these are heading for the table a few times for us
Amazing. What part of the province did these beauties come from?
Time to invest in a hole punch so you and your three buddies can identify who's fish are whos when requested by a CO!
NICE....looks like some Good Eats there . . . . .  . . . .  ENJOY ! ! !
Wow, some crazy fall fishing for ya! What's a hole punch?
Each owner of each fish punches a a hole in a designated fin or section thereof with a prescribed # of punched holes to identify each individual's fish. To keep track of individual possession limits.
I can always tell which are mine, I even give them names.......like breakfast, lunch and dinner.
